vior**\\\\n\\\\nI'm thinking about public classes and whether they have a Serializable marker but aren't really serializing. If that's the case, it could mean direct serialization is prohibited. But then again, I wonder if I can test the `SnapshotVersion` value for equality? It seems like I can, but can I only test that `SnapshotVersion` has equality while others might just be identity? That doesn’t seem to be a feature I can rely on.\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"Implemented a new test in:\\n\\n`tests/src/org.apache.maven/maven-api-metadata/4.0.0-rc-5/src/test/java/org_apache_maven/maven_api_metadata/Maven_api_metadataTest.java`\\n\\nWhat I added:\\n- Analyzed existing coverage: current tests already cover full model construction, defaults, builder collection immutability, direct `with*` copy behavior, builders from existing instances, and `SnapshotVersion` equality.\\n- Added coverage for a distinct feature not directly tested before: collection-valued `with*` methods defensively copy mutable inputs and expose immutable lists.\\n  - `Metadata.withPlugins(...)`\\n  - `Versioning.withVersions(...)`\\n  - `Versioning.withSnapshotVersions(...)`\\n\\nThe new test verifies:\\n- Original instances remain unchanged.\\n- Mutable input collections are defensively copied.\\n- Returned collections remain immutable.\\n\\nI did not modify build files or existing test logic. I did not run tests locally.\", \"textSignature\": \"{\\\"v\\\":1,\\\"id\\\":\\\"msg_01ca6cb4bf2610340169fdf3f6faf8819f9e0bfe70e0c2878b\\\",\\\"phase\\\":\\\"final_answer\\\"}\"}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 868, \"output\": 1417, \"cacheRead\": 32768, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 35053, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"stop\", \"timestamp\": 1778250722949, \"responseId\": \"resp_01ca6cb4bf2610340169fdf3e3d848819fa0d4c2e5365194bc\"}}\nhuman-intervention-logs/org.apache.maven:maven-api-metadata:4.0.0-rc-5/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-08T14-32-24-625049Z.log:6665:[recv] {\"type\": \"turn_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"**Evaluating a new feature**\\n\\nIt sounds like there’s a new feature that involves a mutable builder, which allows changing metadata fields without directly using methods. However, I notice that builders coming from existing instances mean there’s potential overlap with the existing plugin and metadata copies. I'm considering testing Plugin newBuilder(plugin).name and checking if Metadata can be copied the same way. It's a bit similar but not identical, and I wonder if we can keep both options available?\\n\\n**Considering serialization behavior**\\n\\nI'm thinking about public classes and whether they have a Serializable marker but aren't really serializing. If that's the case, it could mean direct serialization is prohibited. But then again, I wonder if I can test the `SnapshotVersion` value for equality? It seems like I can, but can I only test that `SnapshotVersion` has equality while others might just be identity? That doesn’t seem to be a feature I can rely on.\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_01ca6cb4bf2610340169fdf3e489a4819f9ecfb3ac1ab78678\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABp_fP2r6sVyd_TW8v1dMXRVUExtfHLHa5JuYgE-eK8O2plbRhaXdS6Wq2iL0sH7Qrr38J3DCdFfrpSdgDF9KWIK0IpEKZ8f6KPgNGTjEi0skOqfOZCL8PuNaXAxwKaBSYhrBp4MopUlZWmQ1NBVSkc-se3WOmjYG-x6EaHK9PfumT4inSbiGLUt0gF-4iyIYRzUCxdxcrHTUItNKgpPbNWK159yY_NAwMBH60k0LU9-w-8zZM_HYNyiAXPDPYkNe_ViQHfTUn6UdAUdwU3-nFfeX7KWMtN6nvD4zIEEYMOgOLiB5SoiSHjGtY--MB9nsyTdNCZ-1MC6NcDz704g4cNoOkbgNQM5ksmYdwRPD4h1ARK5c2Bu163pA_gP0KMCPRSjPOWqUg2eNmWFQlXjhIJpW3vAerjTAqQSr6ZUDocXyb2xrQW-kw7WzttZMeJ-q2Q0w8NSt-QR3wC2fLe24NyK4l4DpaO9UMqwm6J2MR08DkaUC21c1VKOk_ixHCM8PsTgedE4rzhf3mdlSrVl5hfXaAUu1irgr25a7j6Q1OI6z9hu0nn1IewG-SgtcOQDIxz