alCopy()).isFalse();\\n\\n        assertThat(plugin.getName()).isNull();\\n        assertThat(plugin.getPrefix()).isNull();\\n        assertThat(plugin.getArtifactId()).isNull();\\n\\n        assertThat(snapshotVersion.getClassifier()).isNull();\\n        assertThat(snapshotVersion.getExtension()).isNull();\\n        assertThat(snapshotVersion.getVersion()).isNull();\\n        assertThat(snapshotVersion.getUpdated()).isNull();\\n    }\\n\\n    @Test\\n    void collectionInputsAreDefensivelyCopiedAndExposedAsImmutable() {\\n        Plugin cleanPlugin = Plugin.newBuilder()\\n                .name(\\\"Maven Clean Plugin\\\")\\n                .prefix(\\\"clean\\\")\\n                .artifactId(\\\"maven-clean-plugin\\\")\\n                .build();\\n        Plugin deployPlugin = Plugin.newBuilder()\\n                .name(\\\"Maven Deploy Plugin\\\")\\n                .prefix(\\\"deploy\\\")\\n                .artifactId(\\\"maven-deploy-plugin\\\")\\n                .build();\\n        List<Plugin> plugins = new ArrayList<>();\\n        plugins.add(cleanPlugin);ns(...)`\\n  - `Versioning.withVersions(...)`\\n  - `Versioning.withSnapshotVersions(...)`\\n\\nThe new test verifies:\\n- Original instances remain unchanged.\\n- Mutable input collections are defensively copied.\\n- Returned collections remain immutable.\\n\\nI did not modify build files or existing test logic. I did not run tests locally.\", \"textSignature\": \"{\\\"v\\\":1,\\\"id\\\":\\\"msg_01ca6cb4bf2610340169fdf3f6faf8819f9e0bfe70e0c2878b\\\",\\\"phase\\\":\\\"final_answer\\\"}\"}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 868, \"output\": 1417, \"cacheRead\": 32768, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 35053, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"stop\", \"timestamp\": 1778250722949, \"responseId\": \"resp_01ca6cb4bf2610340169fdf3e3d848819fa0d4c2e5365194bc\"}, \"toolResu